items.reviewContent: There is a fundamental design flaw in this machine.  I have used a moulinex juicer for the past almost 30 years, and it has served me well. In comparison this juicer is very low quality. First the materials used are very low quality plastic which feels like it could break any time, especially the plastic clamps are very thin which can easily become loose. Second and more important, during operation the body of the juicer vibrates, and especially the pulp extractor which is loosely held becomes disjointed, along with it's connected assembly.This results in the juicer turning off automatically. This leads to the operator having to align the parts again to turn it on again. I bought this juicer because of the brand name of Dawlance,known for its reliability, unfortunately it proved to be a completely unreliable machine.My request to return the product was also declined by Daraz saying everything is fine. P.S I'm an EE so have  knowledge about how machines work.
